{{Infobox royalty | name = Abdullah bin Musa'ad bin Abdul Aziz | title = | image = عبدالله بن مساعد بن عبدالعزيز آل سعود.jpeg | image_size = 185px | caption = | full name = Abdullah bin Musad bin Abdul Aziz al-Saud | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1965|2|19}} | birth_place = [[Riyadh]], [[Saudi Arabia]] | house = [[House of Saud]] | religion = [[Wahhabi]] [[Hanbali]] [[Sunni Islam]] | father = [[Musa'id bin Abdulaziz Al Saud]] }}
'''Abdullah bin Musa'ad bin Abdul Aziz'''<ref name="name">{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/espnmag/story?id=3488564|title=The Prince Who Would Be Fantasy King|publisher=ESPN|accessdate=4 September 2013}}</ref> (born 19 February 1965, [[Riyadh]]) ({{lang-ar|عبد الله بن مساعد بن عبد العزيز آل سعود}}) is a [[Saudi]] prince and businessman. He is a son of Prince [[Musa'id bin Abdulaziz Al Saud]] and was appointed Saudi Arabia's General President of Youth Welfare in 2014. He has various business interests including paper manufacturing in his homeland, along with various sporting franchises. He is also the Chairman of [[Sheffield United FC]] Football Club. His half-brother [[Faisal bin Musaid]] was the assassin of [[Faisal of Saudi Arabia|King Faisal]].
==Life and education==
Prince Abdullah, is a son of Prince Musa'ed bin Abdulaziz Al Saud and his mother is Princess Fatima bint Hashim bin Turki bik Alngers of Turkish descent. He was born in 1965 in [[Riyadh]]. Before moving to study in Beirut he returned to Riyadh at the age of ten and studied in the schools of Al Faisaliah. After completing his high school, he moved to [[King Saud University]] studying Engineering of industrial sector and received his bachelor's degree with honours, then got a master's degree in engineering from King Saud University in Riyadh.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.campdenfb.com/article/paper-prince-abdullah-bin-mosaad-abdulaziz-al-saud|title=The Paper Prince: Abdullah Bin Mosaad Abdulaziz Al Saud {{!}} Campden FB|website=www.campdenfb.com|language=en|access-date=2017-04-18}}</ref>
==Business activities== Prince Abdullah bin Musa'ad established a paper manufacturing company in Saudi Arabia (SPMC Group) in 1989,<ref name="paper business">{{cite web|url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/companies/saudi-paper-manufacturing-company-66565.html|title=Saudi Paper Manufacturing Company|publisher=Arabian Business|date=4 September 2013|accessdate=4 September 2013}}</ref> accompanied by some partners, which became one of the largest companies in Middle East, with significant overseas interests. He now owns a 40 percent stake in the operation.<ref name=":0" />
Prince Abdullah was the chairman of [[Al-Hilal FC]] between 2002 and 2004,<ref name="government" /> during which time the club won the Crown Prince Cup. He remains a supporter of the club. In September 2013, he purchased a 50 percent stake in English [[The Football League|football league]] club [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]] and became co-chairman with [[Kevin McCabe (businessman)|Kevin McCabe]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/saudi-prince-buys-50-of-sheffield-united-516440.html|title=Saudi prince buys 50% of Sheffield United|publisher=Arabian Business|date=3 September 2013|accessdate=4 September 2013}}</ref> In February 2018, Prince Abdullah entered into negotiations with McCabe to take full control of Sheffield United.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42995634|title=Sheffield United: Prince Abdullah bin Mosaad bin Abdulaziz Al Saud in talks over buyout|publisher=BBC|date=8 February 2018|accessdate=9 February 2018}}</ref>
==Government== In June 2014, Prince Abdullah was appointed to the position of General President of Youth Welfare in Saudi Arabia.<ref name="government">{{cite web|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/sheff-utd/sheffield-united-prince-abdullah-lands-saudi-youth-role-1-6699351|title=Prince Abdullah lands Saudi youth role|publisher=The Sheffield Star|date=28 June 2014|accessdate=28 June 2014}}</ref>
==Personal life== Prince Abdullah married Princess Jawaher bint Fahd bin Abdullah Al Saud. He has five daughters and two sons.<ref name=":0" /> Princess Sarah is married to Abdullah bin Mute'b Bin Abdullah Bin Abdulaziz Al-Saud, the grandson of King Abdullah. Princess Nouf is married to Saud bin Mansour bin Mute'b bin Abdulaziz Al Saud. Prince Abdullah is known for his love of reading and [[American football]].<ref name="karen">[[Karen Elliott House]], ''On Saudi Arabia: Its People, Past, Religion, and Fault Lines-and Future'', New York, New York: Alfred P. Knopf, 2012, p. 123</ref> He is a fan of [[San Francisco 49ers]], an American football club based in [[San Francisco]].<ref name="buys blades">{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/20130903-announcement-1032027.aspx|title=United secure new international partner|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|accessdate=5 September 2013|date=5 September 2013}}</ref> During the annual football season, he watches the games with friends every Sunday.<ref name="karen"/>
