{{Infobox video game |title= Capitalism II |image= Capitalism II box.jpg |caption= |developer= [[Enlight Software|Enlight]] |publisher= [[Ubi Soft]] |designer= [[Trevor Chan]] |series= |engine= |released= 2001 |genre= [[Business simulation game|Business simulation]] |modes= [[Single player]], [[Multiplayer video game|Multiplayer]] |platforms= [[Microsoft Windows]], [[OS X]] }}
'''''Capitalism II''''' ({{zh|s=金融帝国II|t=金融帝國II|p=Jīn Róng Dì Guó II}}) is the [[business simulation game|business simulation]] [[video game]] sequel to the original ''[[Capitalism (video game)|Capitalism]]''. It was created by [[Enlight Software|Enlight]] and published by [[Ubi Soft]] in 2001.
[[File:Capitalism 2.PNG|thumb|left|''Capitalism II'' in-game.]] The player creates and controls a business empire. This in-depth strategy game covers almost every aspect of business that could be encountered in the real world, including marketing, manufacturing, purchasing, importing and retailing. It has two new campaigns (Capitalist Campaign and Entrepreneur Campaign) plus an in-depth tutorial.
The gameplay is very similar to the original version. One noticeable difference from ''Capitalism'' I is that there are fewer products derived from agricultural resources.
''Capitalism II'' will run on modern versions of Microsoft Windows whereas the previous versions would not.
''Capitalism II'' has also been ported to Mac OS X by [[Virtual Programming]].
A new expanded version of ''Capitalism II'', called ''Capitalism Lab'', was released on December 14, 2012.<ref>http://www.capitalismlab.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=7&t=1144#p5117</ref> ''Capitalism Lab'' has many new features, improvements and a new concept of challenge games.<ref>http://www.capitalismlab.com/</ref> {{clear left}}
