'''Jacob Juma''' (died 5 May 2016) was a Kenyan businessman and government [[critic]] who was born on November 12th 1971 and assassinated in his car on 5 May 2016 by unknown gunmen. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/mfonobongnsehe/2016/05/06/kenyan-tycoon-jacob-juma-shot-dead-in-nairobi/#1dd6d68969c2|title=Kenyan Tycoon Jacob Juma Shot Dead In Nairobi|author=Mfonobong Nsehe|date=6 May 2016|work=Forbes}}</ref> Opposition leader [[Raila Odinga]] claims that Juma's murder was the work of William Ruto.<ref>{{cite news|title=Protests in Kenya|url=https://www.economist.com/news/middle-east-and-africa/21699173-protests-and-repression-bode-ill-elections-next-year-kicking-and-kikuyu|accessdate=21 May 2016|work=[[The Economist]]|date=21 May 2016}}</ref>

